# UUID

Use UUIDs for public-facing record IDs. Prefer server-generated IDs.

## Generation

```ts
// Preferred on server (Node 19+, no dependency)
const id = crypto.randomUUID();

// Or with the uuid package
import { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';
const id = uuidv4();
```

## Drizzle schema

```ts
import { pgTable, uuid, text } from 'drizzle-orm/pg-core';

export const document = pgTable('document', {
	id: uuid('id').primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
	title: text('title').notNull()
});
```

## Validation with Zod

```ts
import { z } from 'zod';

const idParam = z.object({ id: z.uuid() });
```

## Rules

- Never accept client-supplied UUIDs as primary keys unless idempotency is required
- Use `z.uuid()` to validate route params and JSON bodies
- Do not use sequential integer IDs in URLs for user-owned resources
